{"id":3774,"date":"2024-12-17T17:34:52","date_gmt":"2024-12-17T17:34:52","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/?page_id=3774"},"modified":"2025-07-28T01:13:54","modified_gmt":"2025-07-28T01:13:54","slug":"assembling-the-chassis-2","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/assembling-the-chassis-2\/","title":{"rendered":"Assembling the Chassis"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h4>Parts<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to the four <strong>Swerve Modules<\/strong> you built in the previous chapter you will need the following 3D printed parts:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/RobotParts.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"661\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/RobotParts-1024x661.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4519\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/RobotParts-1024x661.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/RobotParts-300x194.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/RobotParts-150x97.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/RobotParts-768x496.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/RobotParts.jpg 1500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus the following hardware and electronics:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisParts.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisParts-1024x573.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4522\" width=\"533\" height=\"298\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisParts-1024x573.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisParts-300x168.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisParts-150x84.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisParts-768x430.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisParts.jpg 1372w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 533px) 100vw, 533px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Note that if you chose to print the parts with the <strong>imbedded nuts<\/strong>, you will only need <strong>two 8-32<\/strong> and <strong>two 4-40<\/strong> inserts.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Assembling the Swerve Modules<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>First attach the two of the <strong>Swerve Modules<\/strong> together using two <strong>1\/2&#8243; 8-32 Screws<\/strong> as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4526\" width=\"400\" height=\"274\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX2.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX2-300x206.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX2-150x103.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX2-768x527.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then in a similar manner attach the <strong>Front Right<\/strong> and <strong>Back Right<\/strong> modules using six more <strong>1\/2&#8243; 8-32 Screws<\/strong> as shown. Since each of the modules has a unique set of nuts\/inserts, make sure you arrange them properly. You can tell which is which by locating the specific screws indicated in the image to the left.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX4-1024x505.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4529\" width=\"477\" height=\"235\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX4-1024x505.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX4-300x148.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX4-150x74.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX4-768x379.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX4-1536x758.jpg 1536w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/SwerveModulesX4.jpg 1621w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 477px) 100vw, 477px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally connect the four <strong>Absolute Encoder<\/strong> cables into each of the four <strong>Encoders <\/strong>as show. Make sure that the labels on the cables match the <strong>Swerve Module<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AnalogEncodersWiring.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AnalogEncodersWiring.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4534\" width=\"435\" height=\"422\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AnalogEncodersWiring.jpg 800w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AnalogEncodersWiring-300x292.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AnalogEncodersWiring-150x146.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AnalogEncodersWiring-768x747.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 435px) 100vw, 435px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h4>Add Screw Inserts To Panels<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>If you chose to print the versions that use inserts you will now need to screw inserts into the two <strong>Panels <\/strong>and <strong>Shooter Mount<\/strong> as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisInserts-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisInserts-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4539\" width=\"525\" height=\"215\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisInserts-1.jpg 937w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisInserts-1-300x123.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisInserts-1-150x61.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ChassisInserts-1-768x315.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 525px) 100vw, 525px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next mount the <strong>Raspberry Pi Mount<\/strong> to the <strong>Pi Panel<\/strong> with two <strong>1\/2&#8243; 8-32 Screws<\/strong> and attach the <strong>Gyro Mount<\/strong> to the <strong>Pi Panel<\/strong> with two <strong>1\/2&#8243; 4-40<\/strong> Screws as shown: <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounts.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounts.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4555\" width=\"360\" height=\"355\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounts.jpg 876w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounts-300x296.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounts-150x148.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounts-768x757.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the<strong> 20 cm Pi Camera Cable<\/strong> to the<strong> Raspberry Pi 4B<\/strong> as shown. Pay attention to the orientation of the cable:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraCable.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraCable.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4565\" width=\"395\" height=\"283\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraCable.jpg 1000w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraCable-300x215.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraCable-150x107.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraCable-768x550.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 395px) 100vw, 395px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then attach the <strong>Raspberry Pi<\/strong> and the <strong>Microcontroller Board<\/strong> to the <strong>Pi Mount<\/strong> as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiMounted.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiMounted-1024x516.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4563\" width=\"594\" height=\"298\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiMounted-1024x516.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiMounted-300x151.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiMounted-150x76.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiMounted-768x387.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiMounted-1536x774.jpg 1536w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiMounted.jpg 1588w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the <strong>Gyro <\/strong>to the <strong>Gyro Mount<\/strong> using two <strong>3\/8&#8243; 2-28 Screws<\/strong> as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/GyroMounted-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/GyroMounted-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4600\" width=\"374\" height=\"360\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/GyroMounted-1.jpg 981w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/GyroMounted-1-300x290.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/GyroMounted-1-150x145.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/GyroMounted-1-768x742.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 374px) 100vw, 374px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>If you choose to print the <strong>Shooter Mount<\/strong> that requires inserts, you should insert them now as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterInserts.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterInserts.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4578\" width=\"406\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterInserts.jpg 827w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterInserts-300x273.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterInserts-150x136.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterInserts-768x698.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 406px) 100vw, 406px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next attach the <strong>Beam Break Sensors<\/strong> to the <strong>Shooter Mount<\/strong> as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/BeamBreakMounted.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/BeamBreakMounted.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4570\" width=\"425\" height=\"351\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/BeamBreakMounted.jpg 1000w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/BeamBreakMounted-300x249.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/BeamBreakMounted-150x124.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 425px) 100vw, 425px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then attach the<strong> Motor Controller<\/strong> to the <strong>Shooter Mount<\/strong>. At this point also connect the power for the <strong>Feeder Motor<\/strong>, <strong>Shooter Motor<\/strong> and <strong>Motor Controller<\/strong> as shown. We connect the power now because, once mounted, the <strong>Motor Controller<\/strong> will be less accessible.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterWiringFixed.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterWiringFixed.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4681\" width=\"399\" height=\"366\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterWiringFixed.jpg 712w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterWiringFixed-300x276.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterWiringFixed-150x138.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 399px) 100vw, 399px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the <strong>Power Distribution Module<\/strong> and the <strong>Circuit Breaker<\/strong> to the <strong>Power Panel<\/strong> using four <strong>1\/2&#8243; 8-32 Screws<\/strong> as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelAssembly.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelAssembly.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4559\" width=\"405\" height=\"411\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelAssembly.jpg 859w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelAssembly-296x300.jpg 296w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelAssembly-150x152.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelAssembly-768x780.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 405px) 100vw, 405px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>It is now time to assemble the remainder of the <strong>Chassis<\/strong>. For this you will need six <strong>2 1\/2&#8243; 8-32 Screws<\/strong>, two <strong>1 1\/8&#8243; 8-32 Screws<\/strong>, six <strong>Long Panel Spacers<\/strong> and two <strong>Short Panel Spacers<\/strong>. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>First attach the<strong> Shooter Mount<\/strong> to the <strong>Chassis <\/strong>as shown. Note that you should use only a single <strong>8-32 screw<\/strong> for now:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterMountMounted.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterMountMounted.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4584\" width=\"422\" height=\"406\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterMountMounted.jpg 1000w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterMountMounted-300x290.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterMountMounted-150x145.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/ShooterMountMounted-768x741.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 422px) 100vw, 422px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the <strong>Power Panel<\/strong> using three <strong>2 1\/2&#8243; 8-32 Screws<\/strong> with two <strong>Long Panel Spacers<\/strong> and a <strong>1 1\/8&#8243; Screw<\/strong> with a <strong>Short Panel Spacer<\/strong> as shown. Do not tighten the indicated screw yet.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelMounted.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelMounted.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4589\" width=\"423\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelMounted.jpg 1000w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelMounted-300x276.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelMounted-150x138.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PowerPanelMounted-768x706.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 423px) 100vw, 423px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the <strong>Pi Panel<\/strong> using three <strong>2 1\/2&#8243; 8-32 Screws<\/strong> with three <strong>Long Panel Spacers<\/strong> and one <strong>1 1\/8&#8243; 8-32<\/strong> <strong>Screw <\/strong>with a <strong>Short Panel Spacer<\/strong> as shown. You can now tighten all of the screws.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounted.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounted.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4593\" width=\"428\" height=\"393\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounted.jpg 1000w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounted-300x276.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounted-150x138.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiPanelMounted-768x706.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, run the <strong>Camera Cable<\/strong> through the slot in the <strong>Pi Panel<\/strong> and connect it to the <strong>Raspberry Pi Camera V1.3<\/strong> as shown. Pay attention to it&#8217;s orientation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraConnection.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraConnection.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4603\" width=\"467\" height=\"301\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraConnection.jpg 902w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraConnection-300x194.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraConnection-150x97.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/PiCameraConnection-768x496.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 467px) 100vw, 467px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then mount the <strong>Camera <\/strong>onto the <strong>Camera Mount<\/strong> using four <strong>3\/8&#8243; 2-28 Screws<\/strong> as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnMount.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnMount.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4607\" width=\"474\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnMount.jpg 1000w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnMount-300x237.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnMount-150x119.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnMount-768x607.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, mount the <strong>Camera Mount<\/strong> to the <strong>Chassis <\/strong>using two <strong>1\/2&#8243; 8-32 Screws<\/strong> as shown. Make sure that the camera is parallel to the front of the robot.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnChassis.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnChassis.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4611\" width=\"475\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnChassis.jpg 1000w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnChassis-300x246.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnChassis-150x123.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/CameraOnChassis-768x629.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 475px) 100vw, 475px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"\/wiring-the-chassis\/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"3904\">Next: Wiring the Chassis<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Parts In addition to the four Swerve Modules you built in the previous chapter you will need the following 3D printed parts: Plus the following hardware and electronics: Note that if you chose to print the parts with the imbedded nuts, you will only need two 8-32 and two 4-40 inserts. Assembling the Swerve Modules&hellip;&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/assembling-the-chassis-2\/\" class=\"\" rel=\"bookmark\">Read More &raquo;<span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Assembling the Chassis<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","template":"","meta":{"neve_meta_sidebar":"","neve_meta_container":"","neve_meta_enable_content_width":"","neve_meta_content_width":0,"neve_meta_title_alignment":"","neve_meta_author_avatar":"","neve_post_elements_order":"","neve_meta_disable_header":"","neve_meta_disable_footer":"","neve_meta_disable_title":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/3774"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/pag